Name: pre-malignant neoplasm
Definition: A disease of cellular proliferation that results in abnormal growths in the body

Name: benign neoplasm
Definition: A disease of cellular proliferation that results in abnormal growths in the body which lack the ability to metastasize.

Name: cancer
Definition: A disease of cellular proliferation that is malignant and primary

Name: obsolete breast fibroepithelial tumor
Definition: A disease of cellular proliferation that is malignant and primary
